                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Tirukkāvalūr Kalampakam</title> by Beschi, a poem in 100 stanzas on Virgin Mary of Tirukkāvalūr. See    Zvelebil (1995, p. 93).</p>
<p>By a Christian copyist, possibly <persName xml:lang="ta" role="owner">Cavarirāyaṉ</persName>, unless he is only the owner.</p>

<p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (October 2021).</p>
<p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p>  

<p>The images are in the reverse order in the Gallica microfilm.</p></summary>
                  
